Bootstrap: docker
From: alisonmacfadyen/sccmecextractor:latest

%labels
    Author Alison MacFadyen
    Email alison.macfadyen86@gmail.com
    Version 1.3.0
    Description SCCmecExtractor: Pipeline for extracting and typing SCCmec elements from Staphylococcus and Mammaliicoccus genomes

%help
    SCCmecExtractor - A toolkit for extracting and typing SCCmec and
    non-mec SCC elements from Staphylococcus and Mammaliicoccus genomes

    Available commands:
      sccmec-pipeline      - Run the complete pipeline (recommended)
      sccmec-locate-att    - Locate attachment sites
      sccmec-extract       - Extract SCCmec sequences
      sccmec-type          - Type SCCmec by mec/ccr gene content
      sccmec-report        - Generate unified report
      bakta                - Run Bakta annotation

    Usage:
        singularity exec sccmecextractor.sif sccmec-pipeline --fna-dir genomes/ -o results/
        singularity exec sccmecextractor.sif sccmec-pipeline -f genome.fna -g genome.gff3 -o results/

    Mount points:
        /data/bakta_db - Bakta database location (only needed for GFF workflow)
        /work          - Working directory for input/output files

%runscript
    echo "SCCmecExtractor Container v1.3.0"
    echo "================================"
    echo ""
    echo "Available commands:"
    echo "  sccmec-pipeline      - Run the complete pipeline (recommended)"
    echo "  sccmec-locate-att    - Locate attachment sites"
    echo "  sccmec-extract       - Extract SCCmec sequences"
    echo "  sccmec-type          - Type SCCmec by mec/ccr gene content"
    echo "  sccmec-report        - Generate unified report"
    echo "  bakta                - Run Bakta annotation"
    echo ""
    echo "Use 'singularity exec' to run specific commands"
    echo "Example: singularity exec sccmecextractor.sif sccmec-pipeline --help"
